<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> make a life for oneself • make a living for oneself</xh5><p> <i>make a life for oneself—</i>construct a good, decent life for oneself (having a job, home, etc.): I don’t feel an affinity to any one place and am willing to move to almost anywhere in order to <u>make a life for myself</u>.</p><p><i>make a living for oneself—</i>earn enough to support oneself: It was a time when a man with sufficient talent and extraordinary energy could reasonably hope to <u>make a living for himself</u> as a freelance writer.</p><p> <i>See also: get a life</i> / <i>get life</i>.</p> </entry>
